# Python tooling: use `uv`

This project uses **[uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/)** for Python workflows. Prefer uv over ad-hoc `pip` / manual `venv` / Poetry as the default path.

## Do this

- Sync/install deps: `uv sync` (with project flags as needed).
- Run commands and scripts: `uv run …` from the repo root (or the appropriate project root).
- Add dependencies: `uv add …` (dev groups per `pyproject.toml` / repo conventions).
- When suggesting setup steps, prefer uv commands instead of “activate venv then pip install” unless the repo explicitly documents otherwise.

Follow CI/Makefile/scripts when they encode a required sequence; for local dev and new instructions, default to **uv**.
